text:
i want to echo some of the sentiments i have been bombarded with this week which have left me feeling both haunting & simultaneously emboldened (an odd combination i know). i have seen & heard many sister survivors voice their truth & share stories of trauma & heartache in a way that is invitational & offers a sense of solidarity to those who have endured similar experiences. sexual assault, rape, violence, childhood abuse & all the ways that people insert themselves forcibly resulting in the harm of others not only baffles my brain but also infuriates me on a cellular level. it gets under my skin into my bones... it’s the motivating force that drives me to stay in this gritty & glorious work of therapy. @embody.therapy
.
.
.
.
i have a desire to keep seeing people of every gender share their intimate stories of survival for the sake of the next generation... to not allow this harm to be stigmatic, perpetuate or stay hidden in the darkness. .
.
.
.
if i ever get the privilege of parenting children of my own• even if i can’t shield them from a cruel & unpredictable world• i will nurture their voices at an early age, to be aware of how valuable their “yes” or “no” is when it pertains to the perimeters of their own bodies. each human should feel a sense of love, safety & belonging to freely express themselves (not at the expense of another’s value or self respect). .
#breakthestigma #sistersurvivors #forwomenwhoroar #traumasupport #feircefighters #nevergiveup #metoo #timesup

text:
#metoo #believesurvivors #ibelieveher

nine years ago this month, i was sexually assaulted at a party. i have gotten fairly comfortable talking about it openly at this point, but writing this right now has me shaking. it’s incredibly unnerving to “go public” to the internet, where you don’t know who is going to see it or what is going to be done with the information. but i have felt compelled to tell my story, in so many words, because of dr. christine blasey ford (a true hero) doing so this past week. and subsequently being disparaged by the media, by men and women, and by people who have no idea what this is like and/or refuse to open their eyes to these realities. 
it was the beginning of my senior year, at a party i had been to numerous times over the previous summer. same house, same interesting drink choices, and never a very big group of people. i was single and very excited about that, ready for my life to be something fun and something different. and all of that came crashing down that night, suffocated under the weight of someone i would have barely called an acquaintance. the girl you see in the above picture was gone, who had spent the evening with her mom and her cousins celebrating at a bachelorette party (where this picture was taken), the most innocent one in that particular group of people… she didn’t cease to exist, but she went into hiding for a long time, and still does to this day. she had gone from being safe with her family to rightfully assuming she would be safe with her friends. because she should have been. 
i went back home the next morning, after sneaking around the house trying to locate my things. literally sneaking because i didn’t know where he was. i ran into him at the stairs and he kissed me on the forehead and then i left. i was scared and confused. i couldn’t remember exact events, just bits and pieces. all i wanted to do was be home, to shower, and to sleep. (continued in comments)

text:
i went to lowe’s and i bought two machetes so that i can make art that fully captures my rage. that is how i feel about this kavanaugh trash, fyi.

open a history book and find out how citizens used to solve problems when their leaders didn’t listen to them. there are worse things we can do than not re-elect them. they shouldn’t forget that. we have a democracy for a reason, and if they don’t like the democratic process, we can always make guillotines trendy again. i mean, or they can just do the bare fucking minimum and nominate a different right wing nut bag who isn’t being accused of sexual assault. 
what does it even cost them? they will only be able to 99% dominate and piss on the libs instead of 100%? whether they get kavanaugh or some other awful dude on their wishlist, the result is the same. but they are so invested in domination and humiliation that being able to win this one is critical to them. can you imagine going through life like that? what sad, disgusting, pathetic people.

#believewomen #ibelievechristineblaseyford #ibelieveher #fucktrump #fucktrump🖕 #fucktrumpsupporters #fucktrumpandfuckyouforvotingforhim #fucktherepublicanparty #socialistfeminism #revolutionaryfeminism #metoo #metoomovement #timesup #timesupmovement #yesallwomen #radicalfeminism

text:
rp @laweekly
•
yesterday, people of los angeles gathered at city hall  with the message, "believe survivors, stop kavanaugh", in the wake of dr. christine blasey-ford's testimony of sexual assault from supreme court nominee brett kavanaugh, hosted by the women's march l.a. foundation @womensmarch . "we need to mobilize now, before the full senate votes early next week, to show senators that their constituents emphatically reject the elevation of kavanaugh to the supreme court and respect dr. ford's courage," the group wrote on facebook. we agree.

kavanaugh's highly publicized behavior of evasiveness and hostile aggressiveness during his testimony has since raised alarms about his temperament being simply unfit for lifetime appointment on the supreme court.  although a newly launched investigation into the allegations against kavanaugh from multiple women is now underway, the scope of that investigation has now been suspiciously throttled by the current white house administration. 
#believesurvivors #metoo #stopkavanaugh #ibelieveher #christineblaseyford #survivor
#boyswillbeheldaccountablefortheiractions 
#realmendontsexuallyabusewomen #kavano

text:
all the stories that were not told and all the ones we can learn from. 🕊
・・・
she was raped at the age of 8. her rapist was found guilty, but spent only one day in jail. after he was released, he was murdered. because of this, she became mute for almost 5 years, believing her "voice killed him." "i killed that man because i told his name. and then, i thought i would never speak again, because my voice would kill anyone ..." her name was marguerite ann johnson. later in life, she would change her name to maya angelou.

during this time, this period of suffering, this period of shame and guilt, this period of silence that she "developed her extraordinary memory, her love for books and literature, and her ability to listen and observe the world around her." a teacher and friend of the family helped angelou speak again, introducing her to the world of books with authors such as charles dickens and william shakespeare.

when she finally did speak, she said she had a lot to say.

maya angelou became a voice for women, a voice for the black community, garnering respect and admiration for her honesty.

she would say, "there is no agony like bearing an untold story inside of you." angelou was challenged by her friend, author james baldwin, to write an autobiography, which became "i know why the caged bird sings". the book would be critically acclaimed, but banned in schools and libraries because of its honest depiction of rape.

when asked by an interviewer why she wrote about the experience, she indicated that she wanted to demonstrate the complexities of rape. she also wanted to prevent it from happening to someone else, so that anyone who had been raped might gain understanding and not blame herself for it.

she would also later write another book titled "letter to my daughter", which was dedicated to the daughter she never had but sees all around her.

in the book, she says, "you may not control all the events that happen to you, but you can decide not to be reduced by them." #mayaangelou #stillirise  #iknowwhythecagedbirdsings #timesup #metoo #wetoo #ownup #womenempowerment

.

.

text:
this was supposed to be a fun photo. nothing serious. eye candy. thirst trap. witty tag line. a no-brainer.

but it has not been a fun week. like millions of women and sexual assault survivors across the us, this last week has left me incredibly raw and on edge. my experiences, thankfully, have been, for the most part, nonviolent. but i still carry them deep inside me and the events of this last week definitely brought it out in the form of anxiety attacks more than once over the last few days. yes, i was ‘triggered’. i punched my first boy when i was 5. he chased me around the playground until he caught me and kissed me. so i punched him. i was sent to the principals office while he continued recess then went back to class. the lesson was clear. boys will be boys, girls get in trouble for fighting back. 
this was, of course, the only innocent occurrence. once i reached my early teens, the harassment quickly became sexual. i never told anyone for a number of reasons. namely that girls are conditioned from an early age to be accommodating to boys, that it’s our responsibility to dress in a way that doesn’t make teenage boys horny or grown men leer, and we’re certainly not supposed to do anything to give them an erection like, say, being in the same room with them for more than 10 seconds. instead of teaching men not to rape, women and girls are still taught how to not get raped, which just means we’re passing our would-be rapist on to his next target.

we currently have a president who has been accused of sexual assault by 19 women, including the violent rape of his first wife, and has openly bragged about grabbing women by the pussy. now he’s trying to appoint someone to a lifetime appointment on the highest court in the land who has also been credibly accused of sexually assaulting women. his accuser had to move her family due to death threats simply because she wants to prevent her attacker from getting a promotion that would grant him lifetime power over the lives and bodies of women.

it’s not about politics. it’s about the unbelievable hatred of women that so many men harbor. these men have power and they use it to control others. (continued in comments)

text_retweet:
#repost @lenadunham #love #pic #women #metoo
・・・
the last few days have been brutal, as we’ve watched a remarkably brave woman be strong armed by cowardly fools who aren’t fit to shine her shoes. i know it’s triggered pain in all of us, each of a different variety, but there is a common thread: shame. shame is destructive. shame kills. i have shame about my assaults. i have deep and impenetrable shame about when i’ve allowed my mind to be colonized and i’ve shamed another woman (may i learn from this shame. may i walk in the light. may i honor her, honor women always.) i have shame about speaking up and shame about staying quiet. for me the antidote to shame is connection. today my brave best friend spoke about her own assault. she’s the coolest, smartest and funniest woman around. may you all hold each other close and remember you are part of a coven. i love you, i really do. 📷 by @mcleanstephenson #justice #usa #picoftheday

text:
☝️at age 17, i fortunately was allowed to skip 12th grade (from my racist redneck south florida high school, which i only attended for 10th grade... did 11th grade in middle east), and did my 1st year of college at university of miami.
one night, at a party at the ground floor dorm apartment of a guy i was dating, i was drugged and then raped in the backyard by one of his football player friends.
i was so out of it i have no idea how i managed to drive back home to my parents’ house where i was living that year.
i didn’t recall that experience nor realize i had been raped until more than 30 years later.
i never told anyone about this until very recently.
i’ve also had other several experiences of being sexually harassed in the decades since then.
watching the hearings with christine blasey ford and this deplorable lying asshole kavanaugh has been very powerful for me and many new ptsd symptoms and memories are still coming up.
#metoo.
#imasurvivor 
#ibelievesurvivors 
please #registertovote #vote

un premier épisode dans la thématique petites #histoiresextraordinaires 
oh ça ne dure pas longtemps ! moins de 10 minutes 😁

10 minutes pour introduire (mon dieu quel mot !) "bernard", un ange gardien, mon surmoi ? ou le fameux ami imaginaire qu'ont parfois les enfants ?  je ne sais pas... pas encore ! bref, celui qui m'a accompagné durant des années jusqu'à ce que je devienne adulte. beaucoup de choses à dire sur lui mais chut... tout cela je le garde pour la suite 😅

a écouter via le site, sur #ausha ou sur #itunes (et bientôt d'autres plateformes)

text:
we are very excited to announce that bianca blu will be supporting the #weupwomen tour honouring remarkable women who have helped others achieve goals. the categories of the awards include innovation, business, philanthropy and caregiving. bianca blu's honorees at the event will be dressed in our latest designs. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
weup is a gamified app that pays you to stick to personal goals and solve social problems. leading up to the app's release in 2019, weup has launched a 10-city marketing tour called #weupwomen honoring distinguished women who have helped others achieve goals.the tour will capture impact stories about women who’ve helped and contributed to other people striving to achieve their goals. the movement uses good news as a way to counterbalance the rising culture of us versus them, men versus women. a way to acknowledge, come together and transform #metoo into #weupwomen.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
weup is a family owned company co-founded by tedx speaker and ceo ramona wright and visionary founder voltaire xodus.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
join us for this wonderful event on 4th october in london. to learn more and book your tickets visit www.weuptheworld.com and follow @weupwomen.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text_retweet:
#repost @myrihla
・・・
i thank god for the gift of reading maya angelou's letters to my daughters this summer. maya never had a daughter but she gave voice to millions of women and generations after her. her legacy lives on #timesup #metoo #believesurvivors  one of my favourite extracts from the book - "mr wilkerson asked me to read a section, which ended with the words 'god loves me.' i read the piece and closed the book. the teacher said, 'read it again.' i pointedly opened the book, and a bit sarcastically read, 'god loves me.' mr wilkerson said, 'again.' i wondered if i was being set up to be laughed at by the professional, older, all-white company? after about the seventh repetition i became nervous and thought that there might be a little truth in the statement. there was a possibility that god really did love me, me maya angelou. i suddenly began to cry at the gravity and grandeur of it all. i knew that if god loved me, then i could do wonderful things, i could try great things, learn anything, achieve anything. for what could stand against me, since one person, with god, constitutes the majority? 
that knowledge humbles me today, melts my bones, closes my ears, and makes my teeth rock loosely in my gums. and it also liberates me" ❤❤❤ #mayaangelou
name: Adéyínká Adébáyọ̀

text:
we are very excited to announce that bianca blu will be supporting the #weupwomen tour honouring remarkable women who have helped others achieve goals. the categories of the awards include innovation, business, philanthropy and caregiving. bianca blu's honorees at the event will be dressed in our latest designs. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
weup is a gamified app that pays you to stick to personal goals and solve social problems. leading up to the app's release in 2019, weup has launched a 10-city marketing tour called #weupwomen honoring distinguished women who have helped others achieve goals.the tour will capture impact stories about women who’ve helped and contributed to other people striving to achieve their goals. the movement uses good news as a way to counterbalance the rising culture of us versus them, men versus women. a way to acknowledge, come together and transform #metoo into #weupwomen.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
weup is a family owned company co-founded by tedx speaker and ceo ramona wright and visionary founder voltaire xodus.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
join us for this wonderful event on 4th october in london. to learn more and book your tickets visit www.weuptheworld.com and follow @weupwomen.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
bishop resigns from church after erectile dysfunction diagnosis

italy: marksfield, a bishop at a church in italy, has voluntarily relieved himself from all his duties soon after he was diagnosed with erectile dysfunction. although pope francis could not understand the connection between the bishop’s responsibilities and the disease he has accepted the resignation, assuming that it is because marksfield wishes to take care of his health.

almost a week later, a delegation of global church leaders had a meeting with the pope behind closed doors (without nuns this time) over the increasing cases of sexual allegations against bishops.

marksfield isn’t the only catholic priest who has resigned recently, but many bishops who have been alleged of sexually harassing nuns and children were forced to submit their resignations too. however, markfield’s reason for quitting is totally bizarre. “he has lost the connection to the almighty with this disease. he who cannot arise himself, how will he arouse the public?” said the bishop who replaced marksfield.

text:
jag har skördat årets matodling. då hittade jag denna morot.
jag tänkte först skriva något sarkastiskt, lite elakt, om bild 2. sen råkade jag vända på moroten och såg framsidan. (bild 1). moroten ifråga vet inget om livet, annat än att jorden den fick växa i, var för hård, och den har försökt skicka ut flera trevare men tydligen stött på motstånd och det stannade vid försök. 
jag ser ju inte bara en morot. jag ser en morotsversion av stenålderns dualistiska fertilitetsfigurer som ser ut som en kvinna från ena sidan, och som en fallos från baksidan.  den symboliserade fortplantningen, som sker med en kvinna och en ykromosom. det är vad som behövs. för mig symboliserar den att män egentligen är kvinnor, eftersom alla foster är kvinnor,  med anlag för vulva, livmoder och äggstockar, tills en punkt när de som har en ykromosom växer åt ett annat håll och får testiklar istället. kvinnan är först. hönan är först och ägget kom sen. hönan kan göra ett ägg,  men ägget kan inte komma ur ingenting. hönan kommer ju från föregående steg i utvecklingsträdet.

kvinnan är grunden, det första könet, mannen är biologins svar på behovet av genblandning. biologin kräver att vi blandar olika gener,  gör vi inte det, blir det inavel och missbildningar och sjukdomar. biologin, dvs livet, kräver genblandning och multikultur. själva livet är emot nazism och rasism och könsförtryck. 
hon var först, gudinnan dyrkades före yehova, i många tusen år. kvinnan hade makten. kvinnor styrde i det mäktiga mesopotamien, där kärlek och samarbete var regel  sen togs landet över av makthungriga patriarker som kom vandrande från norr och tyckte att detta landet var fint, det äger vi. sen fick vi  4 000 år av förtryck som ska ta slut nu.  ut med rasisterna och nassarna bort från icas parkering, dit de kom när de skulle "äga göteborg". sorry men icas parkering är ingen plats med makt över stan. ut med nassarna ur riksdagen och bort med tassarna från våra rättiigheter. 
#ståuppföraborträtten #ingarasisterpåvåragator #statement #metoo #kvinnokraft #feminism #krossarasismen #krossakapitalismen #krossapatriarkatet #patriarkatetskafallaunderminlivstid #dagensrant

(bild 1). moroten ifråga vet inget om livet, annat än att jorden den fick växa i, var för hård, och den har försökt skicka ut flera trevare men tydligen stött på motstånd och det stannade vid försök. 
jag ser ju inte bara en morot. jag ser en morotsversion av stenålderns dualistiska feilitetsfigurer som ser ut som en kvinna från ena sidan, och som en fallos från baksidan.  den symboliserade foplantningen, som sker med en kvinna och en ykromosom. det är vad som behövs. för mig symboliserar den att män egentligen är kvinnor, eftersom alla foster är kvinnor,  med anlag för vulva, livmoder och äggstockar, tills en punkt när de som har en ykromosom växer åt ett annat håll och får testiklar istället. kvin är först. hö är först och ägget kom sen. hö kan göra ett ägg,  men ägget kan inte komma ur ingenting. hö kommer ju från föregående steg i utvecklingsträdet.

kvin är grunden, det första könet, mannen är biologins svar på behovet av genblandning. biologin kräver att vi blandar olika gener,  gör vi inte det, blir det inavel och missbildningar och sjukdomar. biologin, dvs livet, kräver genblandning och multikultur. själva livet är emot nazism och rasism och könsföryck. 
hon var först, gudin dyrkades före yehova, i många tusen år. kvin hade makten. kvinnor styrde i det mäktiga mesopotamien, där kärlek och samarbete var regel  sen togs landet över av makthungriga patriarker som kom vandrande från norr och tyckte att detta landet var fint, det äger vi. sen fick vi  4 000 år av föryck som ska ta slut nu.  ut med rasisterna och nassarna bo från icas parkering, dit de kom när de skulle "äga göteborg". sorry men icas parkering är ingen plats med makt över stan. ut med nassarna ur riksdagen och bo med tassarna från våra rättiigheter.

text:
dans un contexte où les agressions et harcèlements sexuels sont de plus en plus abordés dans le discours public, on pourrait croire comme aiment à le dire certains détracteurs du mouvement me too que la place des femmes dans l'espace public, en tant qu'êtres humains à part entière dignes de respect, va de soi. 
force est de constater que ce n'est pas le cas.
voilà mon témoignage à chaud à propos d'un incident qui m'est arrivé hier, rien de bien construit ni structuré.
je me refuse tout simple de quelque manière que ce soit à perpétuer cette culture du silence et de la culpabilité de la victime.
après tout, j'étais assez reluctante à aborder ceci parce que je me suis directement dite qu'on allait trouver des raisons pour m'incriminer.
est-ce que j'exagère ?
comment étais-je habillée ?
comment dansais-je ?
cherchais-je l'attention ?
stop
je ne suis pas celle que l'on doit blâmer
celui qui m'a ainsi animalisé, mis à mal mon statut d'être humain est celui qui doit l'être

text: eskort. finare ord än hora kanske. låter liiiite bättre att ”byta tjänster” med och ”ge gåvor” till en eskort. istället för att köpa sex av en hora. okej vi leker med tanken. en torsk som heter till exempel lennart skriver ”hej jag skulle vilja veta dina priser och tjänster, vill träffa en eskort för regelbundna utbyten”. låt mig nu säga att exemplet är ett ordagrant citat från min inbox på kik, men namnet på snubben va något annat. okej, jag är en eskort, en ”sällskapsdam”. vi pratar lite till och han frågar om jag gör detta under tvång eller för nöjes skull. ”nytta kombinerat med nöje”, blir mitt svar. vi kommer överens om en avsugning i hans bil och att jag får 500kr för det. han prutar ganska hänsynslöst och tvärt eftersom jag ursprungligen bett om 1500kr. när han hämtar mig på adressen han fått ser han att det är ett kebabställe. klockan är 11 på morgonen och jag sitter där och häller i mig öl. han skriver ”nu är jag framme” och jag vinglar bort till hans bil. stinker öl, sluddrar när jag pratar, har röda utslag av alkoholmängden. vi kör in i en skog, han får sin avsugning och jag mina pengar. så var det med det ”sällskapet”. ett mekaniskt utbyte med en tjej som behöver pengar och som är uppenbar alkoholist och uppenbart avtänd. som förhandlat kaxigt och förlorat striden om priset, som kanske skrivit ”jävla snåljåp” innan hon ändå gick med på det. men lennart känner inte att något i den här situationen är orimligt. han fick en avsugning av en hora och kom billigt undan. hoppsan, han ”bytte tjänster” med en eskort menar jag. och gav en ”gåva”. #metoo #prostitution #utanskyddsnät #intedinhora

a thousand times

i will not speak,
i will roar.

so, now next time you 
question my audacity,
remember:
'my thoughts, are not mere
quiet thoughts.
they are the battle cry.' - shaivya singh

text:
in questo periodo in cui i media ci inondano di pessime notizie incentrate sulla violenza verso il genere femminile, non possiamo esimerci come scuola di wing chun dall’alzare la voce. ogni arte marziale insegna la disciplina ed il rispetto. la nostra però è frutto del cuore di una donna, la badessa ng mui e di quanto essa abbia voluto cedere i segreti della sua disciplina per salvare la vita e la dignità di un’altra donna, yim wing chun, preda di un malfattore.
grazie all’ intelligenza di queste due donne e degli uomini che ne hanno ereditato la sensibilità e la forza, milioni di persone nel mondo oggi praticano il wing chun, avendo la possibilità di crescere fisicamente, ma soprattutto spiritualmente e nel rispetto reciproco. il wing chun è praticabile proficuamente aldilà del genere.
e tu? cosa aspetti a provare?!😉
____
in this period when the media floods us with bad news focused on violence against the female gender, we can not fail as a school of wing chun to raise the voice. every martial art teaches discipline and respect. but ours is the fruit of the heart of a woman, the abbess ng mui and how much she wanted to gift the secrets of her discipline to save the life and dignity of another woman, yim wing chun.
thanks to the intelligence of these two women and to the men who have inherited their sensitivity and strength, millions of people in the world today practices wing chun, having the opportunity to grow physically, but above all spiritually and in mutual respect. wing chun is profitably practicable beyond the genre.
and you? what are you waiting for to try?! 😉

text:
females to the front // tees with a purpose project with @ownsitbyanna 💜⁣
⁣
anna and i are so excited to share our new project. we are giving back in support of females who are experiencing hardship by donating 10% from every tee sale. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
both anna and i have been there, we’ve experienced heartache and trauma through the loss of loved ones, exposure to addiction and to family violence. as females, we live the same joys and challenges as you.⁣⁣ ⁣
⁣⁣⁣
together we feel so passionate about supporting women. it sits deep within our hearts and we hope that with each donation, we can alleviate some of the heartache for our fellow females. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
our nominated charity is wishin - a social change organisation working towards gender equity for all women and children who have experienced homelessness, family violence and related traumas.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
we are so proud to deliver this project. to be a voice for those that feel they don’t have one. females to the front recognises that we are all worthy, none of us are any more or any less than the other and that together we are great. ⁣
⁣
internationally, purple is a colour symbolising women so we chose this beautiful lilac with purple lettering to represent 💜⁣
⁣⁣⁣
tees are available in size xs - 5xl to shop tomorrow night monday 1 october at 8pm aest. if your size is sold out via our website, pop over to @ownsitbyanna as it might be available there. we thank you for supporting our cause 🙏🏽
.
.
#femalestothefront #instafashion #outfitoftheday #metoo #womensupportingwomen #girlsrule #girlssupportinggirls #slogantees #sydneyfashion #realwoman #goodcause #fashionstyle #tshirt #statementtee #slogantee #confettirebels #ownsitbyanna ##motivation #metoomovement

" #billcosby took my beautiful, healthy young spirit and crushed it. he robbed me of my health and vitality, my open nature and my trust in myself and others," - #andreaconstand 🤓...please keep in mind the alleged assault took place in january of 2004. she admitted she was confused on if the alleged assault happened in january or march.
1.) in 2006 andrea constand settled with bill cosby in civil court for 3.4 million dollars. 
2.) andrea constand said she felt “vindicated” after she won the civil suit in 2006
3.) on december 30, 2015 cosby was charged with three second degree felony counts of aggravated indecent assault as a result of the accusations made by constand about the january 2004 incident
4.) when asked why she had dinner with cosby and returned to his house after the alleged assault, she said she wanted to know why he did it. this took place in march of 2004. on this night she asked bill cosby to a concert with her...and her parents. 
5.) andrea constand gave 5 conflicting statements in 2017...well...she lied...and that triggered a mistrial. 
6.) after the alleged assault in 2004...andrea called bill twice on valentines day. 
7.) andrea constand drove to cosby’s house in connecticut on 2 occasions and went in through the back door. on other occasions they stayed at the same hotel...in connecticut. 
8.) during the most recent trial she lied under oath about lying down on bill cosby’s hotel bed. 
9.) she secretly recorded bill cosby. and she secretly recorded marilyn gordon...a person she had dinner with on the alleged night. actually...she said her mother recorded ms. gordon. but...she testified and told police she didn’t have anything to eat that night. 
10.) in her testimony in her civil suit in 2006...she stated that she had physical contact of an intimate nature with bill cosby pryor to the alleged incident. 
11.) andrea constand stated that she went to bill cosby’s house five times...the first time...he touched her thigh...and she went back 4 more times. on the fourth time he unzipped her pants...and the fifth time is when the assault occurred.

text:
what is rape culture and why is it a problem that boys benefit from and women suffer the consequences from?
.
rape culture is a thing. and boys and men are socialized to embrace it and celebrate it.
.
“rape culture is an environment that breeds characteristics which increase the likelihood that sexual harassment, assault, and rape will occur, through the justification that certain acts are not actually sexual offenses.”- @sociologistray
.
acts such as catcalling, locker room guy talk about women, their bodies and sexual exploits, rape jokes, non-consensual pictures and videos, following/stalking, unsolicited flashing and dick pics, groping, cooing a feel, stealthing (covert condom removal), and victim blaming instead of realizing that about 95% of survivors are telling the truth.
.
collectively, these type of acts lead to the permission and acceptance of more heinous acts like drugging (including covert alcohol giving), sexual coercion, and rape.
.
what makes rape culture especially heinous at all levels is that what’s missing from the equation is women’s consent, their feelings, their humanity, and their own control over what happens to their bodies and mental and emotional health during and after these acts.
.
.
.
.
.

this week has been so difficult. watching the hearing and every piece of news we can find on the kavenaugh nomination is like a train wreck. we can't look away but it is guy wrenching to witness. 
women all over the world are reliving terrible experiences of their past at the hands of men. it is exhausting, triggering and so very painful. 
this is, however, the feminism we need. we aren't just seeking equal pay and opportunities. at the heart of feminism lies the cold truth of the danger we face by simply being female. until this is addressed there will only ever be surface changes.

we do not belong to you. we are not less than you. we are uniting in a way which has never been seen before. our painful truth is galvanizing. if you are afraid of this then you damn-well should be. 🤛 📷:@many_bothans .

text:
i didn't report it for the same reason i didn't report any of the other times i was violated or abused. 
because shame is a beast. 
and because of people like you...not you, but you....you know who you are. 
the one's who are looking for a reason not to believe someone's story, because it doesn't resemble your own, or because it sounds so "unbelievable", or because you're just a good old fashioned asshole. 
because the people like you, who need something to make sense to you in order for it to be true for someone else. 
because rapists and abusers are rarely brought to justice within our corrupt systems. 
because i wouldn't have been protected enough to come forward because of the laws made and the bills passed by people like you. 
because people like you, who are looking for a reason to slut shame a beautiful woman who is comfortable with her cleavage. 
because people like you, who have the audacity to tell a child they were blowing it out of proportion or  asking for it. 
because of people like you, who make another person's worst nightmare about you. 
i stand united with my sisters around the world as we each step forward in our own time and in our own way with our hands shaking to type these messages to share with you. 
and i thank each and every one of them for their courage, their strength, and their vulnerability. 
i see you. 
i hear you. 
i believe you. 
i love you. 
we didn't report it because of people like you.

text:
someone (anyone know the source?) compiled a list of 20 preventative measures for men who have expressed their concerns about being falsely accused of rape, sexual assault, sexual harassment, or sexual misconduct: 
1. don’t put yourself in compromising situations.

2. stay alert and aware at all times. if you are at a party with a woman who you think will falsely accuse you of sexual assault, limit your alcohol consumption. she is free to drink, but your impaired judgment is not an excuse for her false accusations. 
3. if you walk or jog for exercise, try to vary your route and time on the street. to be predictable is risky. don’t give women the opportunity to falsely accuse you by having an exercise routine. 
4. keep your body covered. if you expose certain areas of your body she may get the impression you are interested in sex with her. don’t give her that impression by revealing more of your skin than necessary. modesty is the best policy.

5. think before you talk. flirting with a woman is fine but be careful not to give her the impression you’re interested in sex. chaste words will help you maintain your virtue and good name.

6. don’t make yourself an easy target. hold your head up, walk confidently, directly and at a steady pace away from the woman you think may falsely accuse you of sexual misconduct. don’t forget, you’re a strong capable man too. 
7. attract attention to yourself if you feel like you might be falsely accused of sexual misconduct. make noise, call 911, use a whistle in hopes that some one will come to your aid as a witness. you can get “falsely accused of rape” whistles at your local shelter. 
8. if you are being followed, head for a well-lit area where you think there will be other people who may be able to help you. well-lit areas could be the difference between a pleasing evening stroll or a night that will forever change your life. 
9. it’s probably best to stay home after dark. if you’re worried that while you’re walking home at night you might encounter a woman who may falsely accuse you of sexual assault, it’s best to avoid that situation completely. consider a self-imposed curfew.

„auch wenn man als frau anscheinend immer damit rechnen muss und es das schlimmste zu sein scheint, was passieren kann, ist es doch nichts, was wirklich geschieht. so wie es keinen krieg in deutschland gibt oder man ständig angst haben muss zu sterben. vergewaltigung passiert anderen leuten.“ *** vor einigen wochen habe ich (für die veranstaltung am @goetheinstitut_barcelona) "nichts, was uns passiert" von bettina wilpert (@verbrecherverlag) gelesen, nicht nur das buch zu #metoo, sondern auch zu #whyididntreport - die protagonistin anna bereut nämlich schnell, dass sie ihre vergewaltigung angezeigt hat. denn das macht für sie alles noch schlimmer. aber was geschah wirklich in dieser nacht? schenkt man jonas glauben, war der sex einvernehmlich. die freunde und die ganze stadt sind dazu gezwungen, position zu beziehen, während das gerede danach für beide (auch für anna, again: why i didn't report) fast noch schlimmer ist. was wirklich geschah, erfährt der leser nie, da die autorin ihre figuren die ereignisse nur nacherzählen lässt, ohne ihre wahren gedanken zu offenbaren. so muss jeder selbst entscheiden, wem er oder sie glauben schenken will. *** ein richtig gutes buch, eben weil offen ist, was wirklich geschah, und endlich ein roman, der eine vergewaltigung als zentrale thema hat. nicht nur, aber auch der aktualität wegen wirklich lesenswert. große empfehlung! *** #bettinawilpert #nichtswasunspassiert

text:
amongst all of the media and political shit storm, who is thinking or even caring about the victim? once the public row dies down, who will be picking up the pieces of her life? all of us are xhisiela, she is our daughter, wife, sister, aunt, cousin, friend, colleague, and woman we pass on the street. this is not about political tit for tat, it's about protecting women, protecting citizens, and ensuring we have the right to pursue the full recourse of the laws regardless of who our abuser or attacker is related to.

whether you are albanian, foreign, male, female, or whatever your political persuasion, you have a duty to defend humanity.

text: on sundays i share a personal prompt to think or talk on called sunday feels. today’s sunday feels is about believing survivors. because of the sensitive subject matter i don’t want to ask any questions of you (though please engage below if you can/want to). but i do want to say to those of you hurting right now, that you aren’t alone. there is a lot of noise and are a lot of opinions being thrown around. things like “protect your boys, women’s lies could ruin their lives.” this talk reinforces why you haven’t told. i know. and i’m sorry. whether you tell or don’t tell i understand and i believe you. if you want to engage you can comment here, dm me, tag a friend, send to a friend, or just take a moment to reflect by yourself. #tjmsundayfeels #thejonesmarketlife #metoo #believesurvivors #believewomen

text:
this post is extremely personal, painful and probably not something everyone is comfortable reading. 
they say you don’t know what strong is until strong is the only choice you have. two years ago today i was raped. i don’t remember everything from that night (no i wasn’t intoxicated), from the hour the assault went on for, i have memory of about 15 minutes. i remember the fear and the pain. i remember his sweat dripping on me and my tears. i remember locking myself in my car and calling my friend after it happened. i remember her standing by me and supporting me through everything. i still have nightmares and anxiety, but have been lucky to have an amazing support system to listen to me when i need to talk about it. 
when working with the sexual assault advocate she taught me that fear and consent cannot be in the same place. she helped me realize it wasn’t my fault. i didn’t ask for it and didn’t do anything to deserve it. i use writing as my therapy when i’m having a tough day. it’s easier to write what i am feeling than to talk about it. the photos attached are things i have written on some of my bad days; which thankfully are fewer and far between. 
in the end i just wanted to say, don’t judge people because you never know what they are going through. ❤️ #survivor #metoo #ibelieveher #sexualassault #rapeculture #strongerthanyouknow

text:
#whyididntreport #metoo #ibelieveher i did end up reporting that night because an amazing friend drove me to the hospital to make sure i wasn't going to die from head injuries, but i couldn't follow through with the prosecution because; i loved him, we had sex before, i was drunk and went to his house, i was exhausted from the struggle and just wanted to sleep my life away, i felt like i had abandoned my friends and family for him, i didn't feel like i had a home to go back to. 
i didn't understand the spiral it sent me on.... i became an alcoholic drinking almost every single day, i was very flirtatious always craving attention and dating new men. i couldn't keep a relationship with even the kindest person. i kept running and i felt like no matter where i went i had a black cloud over me. i always felt sick and constantly like something was off. i missed and wanted the person who violated me and i didn't understand why. i became this impulsive and emotional person whom i hated.

a crazy and shocking moment was actually just the other day when he emailed me and i saw how easily i ingored it. i realized how strong i've become because of the incident 5 years ago. how i have pushed myself so hard every single day to slap a smile on my face, make myself stronger, make myself smarter,  and make the world around me a better place. do i wish it never happened? yes. am i going to let that stop me from being my best self? no way, never again!

jesus has absolutely transformed me. i'm still a work in progress, but i would never ever want to go back to the way i used to be and i pray that others who have been raped don't let it define them. i pray that they grow stronger than they would have had it never happened. that's the only way to win and not let it defeat you!
-blessings

text:
soap box obligatory bathroom selfie....
i.believe.survivors. child, infant, man, woman and everyone in between. as a survivor myself, i know first hand how difficult it is to come forward with something so dark and hurtful, to have to relive your trauma(s), make yourself completely vulnerable again, be interrogated, not believed, hated, and lose family and friends. it is a wild and harmful process that not many go on. not because what they say happened didn't happen...but because society and most people would rather believe a pleasent lie...that this person who they see and know as good...actually commited a henious crime. and of course the rapist/paedophile/bag of limp chodes...is going to deny any accusations, and drag the victims name through hell and back. of course they will deny what happened, and cry and pray and say what a good person they are. but there are always signs and the truth always wins. for me it stills wins even 24, 20, 16 and 8 years later. 
so, to all the survivors out there. i see you. we're in this together. 
p.s. yes i'm aware that some people have falsly accused others, and that they are no better than those who have actually raped and assaulted people. seeing both sides of the story is the right thing to do, no doubt. however, true accusations always outnumber false ones, and if your first instinct no matter the case, is to say that this person is lying and take the side of the accused...you are no better than them.

text:
to all the women survivors of sexual harassment, you're brave to be fighting the fight: either in courtrooms or with yourself, you are stronger than you believe. i, as i believe almost each and every one of us, have been harassed and kept it to myself. it might take years to come forward or some will never do but never ever blame yourself. the only part where we can plead "guilty" is our existence and that's not something we had a say on. 
i do believe each of you and any of you that needs an ear to listen or a shoulder to cry, feel free to reach out to me.

text:
this image is from "confined", a series on sexual assault, recovery, and reclaimed identity by @kristen.matus_zak. she writes that she is “a woman lost, disoriented, haunted by something deeper, preyed upon by her own subconscious. 
i am here, yet not here. unable to identify; to clarify what’s unfolding in front of me. i was sexually assaulted in 2013 and again in  2015. both instances were forced upon me by people i knew, and both instances left me feeling ashamed, confused, isolated, and powerless. i had lost my voice, my sense of self, and i was void of all emotions. being a victim and a survivor of sexual assault has caused me to feel disconnected from my past life, and i have had to rebuild and rediscover who i am. by inviting the viewer into my personal space, i have given them intimate access to my recovery. being able to control how my narrative is told allows me to re-enter the world and begin to reclaim my identity.” #tootiredproject #metoo #mentalhealthawareness

text: sometimes i get so caught up in my travels that i don’t pay attention to the news and what is going on in the world. most of the time i love it, it gives me a chance to unplug. my screen time is low and my engagement in life is much higher. but right now there’s something that’s been going on that i do want to talk about. if a woman comes forward about abuse or assault the public states, “well that was so long ago it’s in the past, why do we need to ruin this man’s future?” well maybe we should, because i’m sure she thinks about it everyday, i’m sure it has affected every relationship she has ever had and maybe it should ruin his life because i know it has affected hers. maybe in the future the ramifications would be so great that this would never happen again. maybe if we changed the boys will be boys mentality we might actually find that men can act like men.

text:
my friend rosie was brave today. she wrote a letter telling how a pastor sexually assaulted her twenty-five years ago when she was fourteen. her parents were good friends with him so they believed the pastor over their own daughter. what kind of parents would do this? you know the answer—narcissistic people who put themselves and their own needs above their children’s well being. 
after reading her story, i’m not sure which was worse—the sexual assault or the abusive parents. the sad thing is i have at least five other friends with similar experiences. all of these women have never forgotten who did this to them or what happened. burying these events only make them fester. there is freedom in calling out our abusers, but at the same time we need to take care of ourselves. make sure you have emotional and spiritual support when you do this. 
life is only as good as we make it. yes, this world is full of abusers, but there are helpers too. yes, there are people who won’t believe us or attack us for telling the truth, but there are people who will see the truth and stand in solidarity with us. yes, being a warrior is exhausting at times, but love and truth are always worth pursuing. 
stand up for your cause, speak your truth and give your support, but make sure you find some time today to go outside and enjoy nature, or call a friend and go out for coffee, or read a good book. life is manageable and often full of joy when we take the time to appreciate the miracles around us. life is still beautiful! tell your story, but look for the wonder! 
#narcissisticabuse #sexualassault #religiousnarcia #religiousnarcissism #metoo #churchtoo #timesup #wakeupchurch #littleredsurvivor #lifeisstillgood #lifeisstillbeautiful #lookforthehelpers

please save the date! if you would like to be one of our sponsors, or donate your talent for a great cause 
please email us at ripthestigma@gmail.com.

text:
let's talk about mental health, and self acceptance - because life is hard, and maintaining mental health is just as difficult. in particular, i want to say to those in high school or college - you can do it. you do not have to be the best at anything or everything. it's more important to be a happy, healthy individual than to push and stress yourself until you crumble. you do not have to keep any worries to yourself - tell your friends, your family, your teachers, your dog, or at the very least, write it down. in the long run, you don't have to get great grades, be great at sports, or have the most experiences to do well in life. you just need to accept who you are and what you can achieve (and you can achieve more things than you realize with the right mindset). and please- do not hesitate to dm me about anything or everything. i won't judge you, and it might do you good to talk to someone.
-
-
-
-
-
-

text:
‘believe all women’: the problem with hashtag politics

an article by bari weiss in the new york times in 2017 argued that “’believing all women’ can rapidly be transmogrified into an ideological orthodoxy that will not serve women at all.” weiss goes on to argue that the concept fetishizes women in the sense that they become “truth personified”. what is not mentioned however, is that though the ‘believe all women’ concept fits well into a hashtag and is easy and simple to chant at protests, it is once again a simple solution to a complex problem. or more accurately, a plaster to a much more complex and intersectional wound. (link in bio)

text:
"¿le molesta si le hago una pregunta personal?", susurra timothy garton ash, formal pero cálido, en el bar del hotel intersur de recoleta. mi apellido le suena a europa del este y quiere saber más sobre la comunidad judía en la argentina; está fascinado con el modo en que está culturalmente integrada al país. no es de extrañar: este historiador y periodista británico, profesor de estudios europeos en la universidad de oxford, ha dedicado su carrera a examinar los desafíos que propone la combinación entre la libertad y la diversidad, especialmente en lo que respecta a la libertad de expresión. en sus primeros trabajos, el escenario que eligió para estudiar estas disputas fue europa central; en su último libro, libertad de palabra. diez principios para un mundo conectado (tusquets), el lugar donde los conflictos se dirimen es el mundo globalizado e interconectado de la era digital.

garton ash tiene una frase que está en el centro de la argumentación delibertad de palabra: "civilidad robusta". contra las retóricas de la provocación y la agresividad, argumenta que cualquier cosa, por compleja o polémica que sea, se puede discutir en paz si uno se esfuerza por ser "civil" en este sentido de robustez. su forma de hablar es una especie de modelo vivo de sus argumentos. asegura que "corrección política" es un concepto sin sentido, analiza los claroscuros del movimiento #metoo y protesta contra la idea de que el estado nos diga cómo debemos hablar en una democracia: todo esto, con una cortesía tranquila y amena que invita a analizar sus argumentos con detenimiento antes de repreguntar.

su vuelo no vino de oxford, donde enseña y escribe (tiene una columna en the guardian desde 2004 y es un colaborador asiduo dethe new york review of books, además de haber pasado por otros espacios prestigiosos como the spectator y the independent), sino de stanford, california, donde pasó el verano trabajando. está asesorando a facebook en sus procesos de apelación y rendición de cuentas ante usuarios. entre notas, investigaciones, clases y consultorías, se hizo un espacio en la agenda para visitar nuestro país, invitado por el programa argentina 2030 de la jefatura de gabinete de minis

text:
i've seen so many posts saying that mother's should fear girls and women ruining the lives of our sons at any point with a claim of sexual assault. as a mother of an 18 year old young man, i am not afraid. yes, it could unfairly happen but, when a boy is taught consent and how to control himself and respect his own limits, his chances of being targeted are going to drop like a hot stone. the problem is not with our boys being targeted by girls. nope, the problem is that boys get a pass on bad behavior way too often. although i didn't get all caught up in the #metoo movement, like so many women my age, i too have a long suppressed story of sexual assault. and like so many women,  #whyididntreport is that i knew it would be my word against his and nothing would be done. this country needs a cultural shift and it starts with mothers of boys stepping up and teaching our young men what being a good man really is. 
#consent

text: as a medical doctor - midwife i’ve spent decades hearing and helping women heal the stories behind #metoo- stories that were experiences and traumas that sometimes settled deep into body tissue and became a constant reminder to her that her body was betraying her when in fact her body was betrayed. i have felt angry many times when i’ve heard the stories. stories are data with a soul. the data. it’s really a beautiful human and her yoni on the other side of the rape kit i was collecting. the endometriosis in a woman in a violent relationship she doesn’t know how to leave or can’t safely. it’s this and more. and there are #medicalmetoo stories- 10 years to an endometriosis diagnosis, fat shaming, pain dismissed, unwanted cesareans and hysterectomies that we’re also unnecessarily done. anger. it is a fire that inspires us to make change. i also know that i have to find the softness in me so the angers fuels but doesn’t consume. music, art, quotes... they feed my soul while the work happens. so often inspired @yung_pueblo and this is wonderful for welcoming a new week... what keeps you inspired?

text:
spiritually sunday...hang in because it’s long but real and it might piss people off (love always love tho) and well 🤷🏽‍♀️you cant please everyone and if it helps one person (which is always my motto) it’s worth it. 🙏🏽 i was recently told by quite a few people that they don’t believe in god or really anything for that matter. so guess what that will get you? hopelessness. 😔. say what you will and clearly people have their own opinion but here’s mine (opinion that is) you have to believe in something because otherwise you’re done! 
life is going to send you sad times, hard times, rough times and times that you can’t imagine how the hell you will ever get through and if you don’t have something to believe in it’s over. how will you survive and ever be happy? how? 
how will you know that through those hard times come valuable lessons? how will you believe that not forgiving someone hurts you and not them? how will you know that through those rough patches you can find love, support and community of people who will let you know that you’re not alone because #metoo because i guarantee if you’re going through something someone else you know is too. its through those times that we realize that there is something bigger than us, so you don’t have to believe what i believe....just believe that there is something bigger then you...and then you can get through...anything. 🙏🏽🙏🏽❤️❤️❤️

text:
had a great time playing at #thevoid’s rebirth last night! got us talking about venues who make strong, positive choices (yay @voidliferecords!) - and venues who don’t (where do we even begin...) ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ the demand for safer spaces isn’t solely a #metoo rallying cry; it’s *essential* to #equality and just plain good business. enter @waronwomen’s @shawnapotterwow. she knows her shit. her ‘lil handbook #makingspacessafer is a simple guide for creating #safespaces for all and outlines smart business practices that benefit everyone. this a must-read for every business owner. pick one up then check out ihollaback.org to wipe out harassment in your community. #tcb @akpressdistro one for all and all for one. #packmentality #packgoals #feminism #dotherightthing #tcgb
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
now come out and see us today at pointless forest with @unringthebell. doors at 4. oh, and if you know of a venue who doesn’t maintain a safe establishment speak out! we know who you are...

text:
"just because you're clean don't mean you don't miss it" - @taylorswift 💕⠀
.⠀
clean can mean so many things here. every time i hear this song this line hits me. clean from drugs/alcohol. clean from toxic relationships. clean from your eating disorder. whatever you're battling❌‼️⠀
.⠀
being clean means choosing to make a decision that you know is healthy/will benefit you in the long run. being clean doesn't mean you don't crave it, miss it, cry for it, or long for it. being clean doesn't mean you're free of the thoughts and desires.⠀
.⠀
it's okay and normal as we work on ourselves to miss old habits, behaviors, relationships, etc. we engaged in them for some sort of short term comfort and control. it took me a long time to realize this and i still fight it. let yourself grieve.  let yourself miss it.  let yourself be sad. these feelings are valid. normal. okay. understandable. relatable. these feelings won't last forever. but the growth and strength you gain from pushing through and fighting your demons will stay with you forever. ❤️🌈✨🌿🌸
.⠀

text_retweet:
the storm will keep growing as women and men join our actions and our voices against violence and abuse! may our compass be love, our action fierce and our intention harmony! ♥️🔥🙏🏻reposting from a friend i respect #repost @seanecorn with @get_repost
・・・
this is a picture of a vandalized article of my friend @karenavirginia. karena is a kundalini yoga instructor from my home state of nj.  she is also one of the brave women that came forward and accused @realdonaldtrump of harassment before the election. as you can imagine, when she went public her life flipped upside down and the hate she and her family experienced was utterly traumatic. today she posted this picture on instagram with commentary, but once again, was hit back so hard, she was forced to take it down to protect herself and family. in her post she said “i’m done holding secrets society wants held. look what happened to me when i revealed sexual assault on ‘pussy grabber’...i was threatened to death. daily. the death threats were beyond frightening. the lack of support was heartbreaking. how are we contributing to teenagers speaking up when we are afraid to reveal the truth about gurus, priests, spiritual teachers and our communities when they would rather keep secrets secret? how? we aren’t? that is why we are kicking and screaming today...”. with her permission i am posting her pic and a part of her commentary. i stand with karena and all the women who refuse to be silenced. this is not a time for passivity; for waiting for the storm to blow over. we are the storm and we’re not dissipating anytime soon. please show your support for karena by leaving her a message here or on her page. i want her to know that there is support here in the yoga community, and that she is not alone in her efforts and that her voice is welcomed, her experience believed and her spirit valued. #webelieveyou #metoo #whyididntreport #endviolenceagainstwomen #offthematintotheworld @offthemat #silentnomore

text: 🍑 porn // no mercado pornográfico desde 2006, onde começou como produtora, may medeiros passou a dirigir seus próprios filmes e já provou que tem talento pra coisa. ao lado de mila spook e marcello cavalcantti , ela concorre na categoria 'melhor direção' do 5º prêmio sexy hot, uma espécie de oscar do pornô brasileiro. a diretora se destacou com o filme 'bruxas' e falou ao g1 sobre alguns cuidados que tem com suas produções, num mercado predominantemente machista. . . 💬 não tem como pensar em roteiro de filme e não pensar em questões que são importantes para o universo feminino. isso, para mim, é não reproduzir machismo. isso vai acontecer em todos os meus filmes. mas acho que isso todos deveriam fazer". para apoiar hoje.

text:
did you know i was voted ‘most likely to lead a protest’ in high school? you probably didn’t, considering i haven’t posted anything remotely controversial, political, or opinionated here. and that has been by design. the truth is, when my company was younger and smaller i sent out a newsletter (and a post) in support of international women’s day. i was lambasted by enough women that i made the decision to not use my company as a platform for anything that could be deemed controversial or remotely political.  i examined other brands and business owners (bloggers, influencers, ecommerce folks, store owners, etc) and noted that some used their channels as a platform to voice their opinions and others didn’t. i justified my decision by telling myself that my company was too small, too fledgling, too unestablished to alienate any potential customers. but it went against everything inside me to not have a public viewpoint, to not stand for something. my company’s posts have since focused on our products, our team members, and my journey as an entrepreneur. a few posts have been very personal and allowed bagnet’s followers a glimpse at the woman behind the company. aside from those posts, i have maintained a business-only approach to what bagnet shares with our followers. that ended on friday when i posted a photo of dr. ford on instagram that included a quote from the new yorker that draws a parallel between the hill-thomas hearings and the ford-kavanaugh hearings, and what those hearings mean for women and men, respectively.⠀
⠀
that post received 145 comments, some very positive and some highly negative. criticism of that post included the sentiment that a company’s profile is not the platform for anything controversial or political. but it is 2018 and times have changed. entire companies and brands are built around individuals: who they are and what they stand for. facebook, instagram, youtube and twitter have given us a direct line of access to ceos, celebrities, and ... (continue reading via link in bio).⠀
⠀
⠀
#fempreneur #femalefounders #womensupportingwomen #bagnet #believesurvivors #metoomovement #metoo #whyididntreport #ibelieveher #timesup #believewomen

text:
this time 10 months ago i was terrified to leave my house on my own, and terrified to stay home alone as a situation from 7 years ago began to reoccur. i pretty much took up residence in friends house & needed my hand held to get through the day. 
i may still only sleep after triple checking every lock, alarm and camera but in the last few months i started setting goals to get me back to myself again.  i’ve got back out running and trained for 10k on my own, and today completed the @cookminimarathon my own. always remember baby steps go a very long way #metoo

text_retweet:
#repost @ttt_official with @get_repost
・・・
dear women who were silenced,

this is a problematic letter. problematic because it's both an apology and a rally cry. problematic because in this society it's always innocent until proven guilty, unless the accused is a woman demanding justice. because what you've been through, is something most woman have been through at least once in their life, no matter how powerful, rich or famous.

this is a problematic letter because the world keeps telling you to raise your voice, but then stifles you the moment you open your mouth. because the society will call you an attention whore every time you call them out on their pervertedness. because when a man molests a woman, it becomes the woman's responsibility to prove her claim instead of the man's responsibility to defend his innocence.

this is a problematic letter because a man is either too young for his career to be ruined or too old for his reputation to be soiled. if he's rich she's a gold digger, if he's famous she's a power hungry bitch, if he's influential she's just crying wolf, if he's neither she's just another vengeful feminist. this is a problematic letter because there's no justice, worse still, there's no trial. it's all a matter of inconvenience which shall either be forgotten or denied, never given the importance it deserves.

this is a problematic letter, because despite all of it, you've persevered. despite the threats you haven't shrunk away from demanding the truth come out. despite the indifference you've not lost all hope.

this is a problematic letter, but it is also one to remind you, don't stop asking for justice because the world will never stop asking for anything less from you. this is to remind you that your voice might be the one which opens a floodgate of fearlessness. this is to tell you to keep your voice raised, and promise you it'll never be alone in this fight.
.
~ nilesh mondal (@hungover.hamlet)

text:
#kavanaugh is as much of a disgusting pathological liar and sexual predator as #trump. so it stands to reason trump would support him. they seem to forget that we're in the age of google, and their lies can be debunked just by the click of a mouse.

i attended high school and uni with these drunken debauched rich boys and frat boys. they were privileged and entitled, as well as having these feelings that they were untouchable and above reproach. they only looked at girls and young women as if they were things to do with as they wished, and not people. the way most of those guys treated girls and young women was abhorrent. yes there were rapes and sexual assaults on campus and on cue, even when these guys were caught, it was never their fault, it was always someone else and they went straight into victim-blaming. 
then their wealthy parents would hire various $500 an hour assassins to mount a case where the accuser was some evil, scourned young woman with a questionable past, who was simply trying to ruin poor richie rich's reputation and extort money. 
this plays out in every facet of society when women come forward and try to get justice against rich, powerful, well-connected men, especially white ones. it also plays out the same way with average middle class americans. the victims are always lying, even when the evidence proves otherwise. 
kavanaugh exhibited every ounce of that tich frat boy mentality in the hearing. we must dismantle the #rapeculture that permeates throughout society and start believing victims of rape and sexual assault. #believewomen #supportsurvivors #womensmarch #stopsexualassault #timesup #metoo

let's talk numbers here. i don't normally involve myself in politics, and especially not on a business focused venue, but this hits close to my soul because i am a #survivor. 🙇‍♀️
1 in 6 women will be the victim in a rape or attempted rape in her life. 1 in 6. that means someone (maybe more than 1) in your family is a victim of rape. 💖💖💖💖💖💔
every 96 seconds, there is another sexual assault in america. in the time it takes me to type this...another sexual assault has happened. 🇺🇸
individuals in the 18-24 years age range are 92% more likely to be raped or assaulted than those over 65.
👧>👵
students are at a higher risk of sexual abuse or assault than non students, and that statistic carries through all genders, and is exacerbated for transgender students.
👩‍🎓👨‍🎓
94% of women who are raped will experience some form of ptsd.
🧠
7 out of 10 rapes are committed by individuals known personally by the victim. 🧑👩👩‍🏫👩‍🌾👩‍🔧 when i reported my multiple cases of sexual assault by a family member, my claims were turned on me, and i was punished for slandering my 85 yr old grandfather. i was 7. 
#whyididntreport #stopvictimblaming #metoo #ptsd #rape #sexualassault #molestation #woman #stronger #survivor #resist #politicalpartiesdontmatter #actionmatters

text:
i have several #metoo stories.  i was young and insecure and easy prey. all of the horrible things that happened to me sent me on a downward spiral of alcoholism, anxiety, depression and codependency. at some point along the way i decided that enough was enough. i have 2 daughters and i wanted to be a good role model for them. i quit drinking and began to work through some of the negative self talk. 
i picked up tools along the way and discovered that there are many different paths to healing. this is why i created the 1st wise women retreat. you see, i learned that, although there are many different paths, there is one thing that is certain. we get stronger and heal together. we need community. this is the basis of all 12 step meetings. support from others who understand. we need our tribe so that we can lift each other up and catch each other when we fall. 
gaia sisterhood is a safe place to land. we celebrate the seasons of the year, honor the cycles of the moon and most of all, each other. 
join us next weekend, october 5th and/or 6th as we host another event at atmalogy ,teachings of the goddess kali! click on gaiasisterhood.org under goddess gatherings
on october 26, we are co-facilitating and event with freedom folk and soul. dia de los muertos, honoring our ancestors with chili dinner, shamanic breathwork and shrine making! register at gaiasisterhood.org click on gaia circle.
much ❤️ jennifer harvard

text:
a gratifying outlook *

for most of my life, i thought beauty is something that you see, something physical, something that other people approve and express when they like what they see. i learned that to truly feel beautiful, there was something more to it. the notion that one has to be comfortable in their own skin is very true, and to have people and environment surrounding us, that foster and nourish that state, is as important. there isn’t one definition of beauty, it can signify so much. it is up to us to see it within us, in other people and things around us, not just with our eyes but with our brain, mind and spirit. one magical thing that happens following the discovery and realization that everything that surrounds us is beautiful and unique, is that it grows and illuminates to other parts of your life. it reciprocates back with the same energy that we give out. beauty for me is just being content and grateful for that very moment in your life you’re in right now and looking forward to the further discovery of the world and yourself. *

text:
i’ve gotten several messages about this campaign; i enormously appreciate those reaching out and am so happy to see people showing involvement.
i stand by everyone’s choice to express themselves how they want. if silence is how you choose to show your support, cool, no judgment at all.
personally speaking, this feels like “let me voluntarily silence myself while this important and long overdue conversation happens without me”.
i won’t keep quiet.
i can’t.
#silentnomore #metoo #metoomovement #speakupspeakoutstandup
•
•
edit to add: i am not saying, nor would ever say, that survivors *must* speak publicly. everyone is ready at different times, and some may never be. that is perfectly okay.
this is purely in regards to campaigns that seek social media blackouts at a time when our voices matter more than ever.
•
•
•
image via lara b. sharp

text:
🤝вот мы и прикоснулись к истокам. ведь район сити -историческое ядро лондона. сформировалось на месте римского поселения лондиниум. а мы вчера его исходили вдоль и поперек. прогулка удалась, как думаете?

девиз сити — domine dirige nos («направляй нас, господи»). ну, я не претендую, но, как мог, направлял вас и нас. 
что интересного? 
конечно же, тауэрский мост. длина -244 метра. но размер в данном случае значения не имеет. мост - как ворота в лондон. такой весь из себя. старинный, с завитушками по бокам. представляете, когда-то он был шоколадного цвета. идёшь по нему, а он приговаривает: сейчас я тебя съем. а мы, конечно, не из того теста, ну и убежали. 
правда, недалеко. там за поворотом, там за поворотом... там крепость многофункциональная (так бы сейчас сказали). ведь для кого-то это был роскошный дом с монетным двором, а для кого и тюрьма. именно там любвеобильный генрих 8 держал, а после и казнил свою бывшую жены анну болейн. и не ее одну. вот им повезло, что тогда движения #metoo не было. а то генрих бы тогда сам был распят. 
да уж, тауэрская крепость - это настоящий шкаф скелетов английских монархов.  или же шкатулка кащея бессмертного. вместо иглы-ворон. прогони его, и королевство кончится.

а потом, а потом.... суп со знаменитой британской бараниной. как не слышали? не может быть!!!! ну ладно, я тоже не слышал. но почему бы и нет? пусть им будет приятно. как вы поняли у нас обеденный перерыв. 
про вторую часть нашей прогулки напишу, если вы захотите... ))) жду ваших сердечек и записочек. ваш я. 
#лондоннаш #тауэр #тауэрскиймост #жизнь #туристы

text:
men ask why women are so pissed off. even guys with wives and daughters. jackson katz, a prominent social researcher, illustrates why.  he's done it with hundreds of audiences:
"i draw a line down the middle of a chalkboard, sketching a male symbol on one side and a female symbol on the other.
then i ask just the men: what steps do you guys take, on a daily basis, to prevent yourselves from being sexually assaulted? at first there is a kind of awkward silence as the men try to figure out if they've been asked a trick question. the silence gives way to a smattering of nervous laughter. occasionally, a young a guy will raise his hand and say, 'i stay out of prison.' this is typically followed by another moment of laughter, before someone finally raises his hand and soberly states, 'nothing. i don't think about it.'
then i ask the women the same question. what steps do you take on a daily basis to prevent yourselves from being sexually assaulted? women throughout the audience immediately start raising their hands. as the men sit in stunned silence, the women recount safety precautions they take as part of their daily routine.
hold my keys as a potential weapon. look in the back seat of the car before getting in. carry a cell phone. don't go jogging at night. lock all the windows when i sleep, even on hot summer nights. be careful not to drink too much. don't put my drink down and come back to it; make sure i see it being poured. own a big dog. carry mace or pepper spray. have an unlisted phone number. have a man's voice on my answering machine. park in well-lit areas. don't use parking garages. don't get on elevators with only one man, or with a group of men. vary my route home from work. watch what i wear. don't use highway rest areas. use a home alarm system. don't wear headphones when jogging. avoid forests or wooded areas, even in the daytime. don't take a first-floor apartment. go out in groups. own a firearm. meet men on first dates in public places. make sure to have a car or cab fare. don't make eye contact with men on the street. make assertive eye contact with men on the street.”
― jackson katz, the macho paradox: why some men hurt women and how all men

text:
this social moment that has captivated the country, even more so in the last few days, has really been breaking my heart. unfortunately, i’m not always great at using my words to explain what i’m actually feeling. dancing does that for me and this song put everything i’ve been thinking over the past few days perfectly. there’s a moment at the beginning where we all stand and look at ourselves directly in the mirror. fletcher is saying, “it’s that sick to your stomach feeling with a smile on your face.” the video doesn’t do it justice, but it’s such a powerful moment. a moment when all four of us are connecting to something we can all relate to. whether that’s motivational or upsetting in this context, i’m not really sure. 🔹🔹
there’s an article in pointe magazine that says something to the effect of dance as always being tied to activism and anyone who doubts that has their history wrong. i wholeheartedly agree with that sentiment. 🔹🔹
thank you @shelbea_j @_c.chapman_  and @funkymakayla for dancing with me and being strong enough to be vulnerable. your love, silliness, and beauty make the world such a brighter place. 
#ibelieveyou #fletcher #metoo #danceactivism #lyricalchoreography

text:
sorry, i will not be taking part in this female blackout thing. nothing personal but i spent a good portion of my life hiding in shadows, being silent. those days are over. so, i will speak my truth. i will speak my history. i will speak my experiences. i will not back down. and sure as hell will not be silenced.
i realize there are some out there that say i made it all up, that i've forced my daughter to lie about her experiences, and that i am actually the abuser. 
to those people i say, and i mean this with my entire heart and soul, fuck you and your shit brand of jelly. 
why didn't i say anything? because in the beginning i didn't want to believe someone who loved me could do these things. then it turned into threats. if i tell, he'll kill me. if i tell, he'll say it was me and get custody of our daughter. if i tell, he'll kill her. 
oh and i've heard the whole, he would never hurt a fly. ok. you keep telling yourself that. because i remover the holes punched through walls and doors. i remember the smears of blood on my appointment book to remind me what he's capable of. i remember being told how he would drive a truck through the garage of the house i was staying at or fill a trash can with gas, light it on fire and shove it towards my house. 
i will not be #blackedout. i will not be #silent. i did that for too damn long and i will not play that game anymore. women are changing the rules now. so here i am saying #metoo. my daughter too. it's been 6 years since we got out from that and three years since we've seen him. 
and our lives have never been better. 
whether you #comeforward or not, it's your choice. whether you #presscharges or not, it happened. whether there were witnesses or not, it is your experience and your truth. don't let anyone else take that from you.
use that #anger. use that #pain. turn it into #strength and #courage and #standup for people who can't. your story may help someone tell their story. 
i'm refuse to be a #victim. i am a #survivor. i am a #fighter. i will not be silenced.
#domesticviolence #abusesurvivor #nomore

text:
i had my little moth by @colorme.katieleigh freshened up yesterday ♡♡♡
i try to actively avoid mentioning anything vaguely political on social media, for several reasons, but i will tell you there is a #metoo story behind the placement and meaning of this tattoo for me. it's a story i'm not ready to tell, and i might never be. but i do enjoy that people now ask me about this tattoo rather than the nasty scar beside of it on the other side of my wrist. there is an element to getting a tattoo that takes ownership of your body back into your own hands- i get to decide what goes on my body- this was my choice- not a scar inflicted by someone else's choice. and if i choose something to go on my body forever, it will be a beautiful reminder of how much more there is to life.

text:
the @ncadv reports: 20 people per minute are physically abused by an intimate partner in the united states. 1 in 3 women and 1 in 4 men have been victims of domestic violence within their lifetime.
~~~~
the @federal_bureau_of_investigaion reports that 13% of simple assault dv goes unreported and 31% of serious assault dv goes unreported due to fear of reprisal. and the % are probably even higher in reality. ~~~~~~
domestic violence is real, each of us have been effected by it personally or through connection to a loved one. no one is alone in the experience and as we take a stand to be bold in vulnerability and share our stories those women and men who do feel alone will know they are held and supported, you are not alone! your voice matters. ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
by sharing our stories we can stop the cycle of hidden abuse for the generations of our daughters and sons to come
~~~~~~~~~~~
#domesticviolence #domesticviolenceawareness #metoo #yourvoicematters #speakup #youarenotalone #stopdv #womenempoweringwomen #weareallhuman #befamily #standup #wewillnotbesilent
